This paper is primarily focused on computer vision for lane detection, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of this technology for autonomous vehicles, which could also fall under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of neural networks for classification and clustering could also be considered under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of reliable positioning, which could be relevant to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
